Django Philosophies Applied 

1. DRY (Don’t Repeat Yourself)
Used separate models and ForeignKey relationships to avoid data duplication and ensure consistency.

2. Explicit is Better Than Implicit
Used clear field names, relationships, and helper methods like is_open() for better readability.

3.Loose Coupling
Designed independent models (Community, Dwelling, Tenant, RepairRequest, MaintenanceUpdate) to keep components flexible.

4. High Cohesion
Each model has a single responsibility (e.g., Tenant handles resident data, RepairRequest handles issues).

5. Model-Centric Design
Added logic inside models using methods (active_repair_count, get_absolute_url) and validators.

6. Convention Over Configuration
Followed Django’s default structure (models.py, admin.py) and standard practices.

7. Admin as a Powerful Tool
Used Django admin for testing, data entry, and management with list_display, search_fields, and filters.

8. Database-Driven Design
Designed normalized schema using ForeignKey relationships and migrations for structured data storage.
